So far, the Civil Aviation Administration of China has carried out 13 transportation missions to the affected countries, including arranging seven temporary flights to bring back 1,101 Chinese citizens.



REPORTER: Niu Qichang

On the afternoon of March 16,2020, the joint prevention and Control Mechanism of the State Council held a press conference on the prevention and control of the importation of overseas epidemic situations in accordance with the law. Wang Jun, director of the Department of Policy and regulation of the General Administration of Customs, said that the current situation of prevention and control of the domestic epidemic situation continues to be good, but the spread of the epidemic outside China is accelerating, and "import of external prevention" has become the top priority of the current epidemic prevention and control in China.

As of 2400 hours on March 15th, 123 cases had been reported in China, including 15th of March, 02400, a total of 12 cases (4 in Beijing, 4 in Guangdong, 2 in Shanghai, 1 in Yunnan and 1 in Gansu) were newly reported.

The World Health Organization declared the new pneumonia outbreak a global pandemic on March 11, the director of the Border Control Division of the State Administration for Migration, Liu Haitao, said at a news conference, the number of daily arrivals at land, sea and air ports was 120,000, down more than 80 percent from the same period last year. Of these, 20,000 people arrived on international flights every day, with foreigners accounting for about 10 percent.

On March 16, the Supreme Court and other five departments jointly issued the opinions on further strengthening frontier health and quarantine work and punishing Crimes Infringing Upon Frontier Health and Quarantine Laws (hereinafter referred to as "opinions") , it is required to further strengthen frontier health and quarantine work and punish in accordance with the law the illegal and criminal acts of Impairing Frontier Health and Quarantine.

Wang Jun said the opinion requires departments to accurately understand and apply the law when handling cases that harm frontier health and quarantine, and lists six types of acts that harm frontier health and Quarantine, if these acts cause the spread of quarantinable infectious diseases or there is a serious risk of their spread, the offender shall be convicted and punished in accordance with the Criminal Law as "the crime of Impairing Frontier Health and Quarantine" .

Interface News noted that the above-mentioned six kinds of actions include refusing to implement health quarantine measures such as health declaration, body temperature monitoring, medical inspection, epidemiological investigation, medical screening, sampling, etc. , or those who take sanitary measures such as isolation, detention for medical examination, on-site examination, referral, etc. , or who conceal the epidemic situation by not filling in the health declaration card truthfully, or forge or alter quarantine certificates, certificates, etc. .

According to Wang Jun, some immigration officials use various means to refuse to declare their health status, do not cooperate with body temperature monitoring, and even take antipyretics to lower their body temperature and cover up fever symptoms, there is a significant risk to public health and safety if close contacts are infected or quarantined after they have been cleared through the health and quarantine process at customs and have been diagnosed as new crown pneumonia upon entry. "If you try to evade customs quarantine by taking chances, you will not only be condemned by the whole society, but you will also face imprisonment, " Wang Jun said.

A reporter asked, as the overseas epidemic continues to spread, many Chinese hope to return to the country as soon as possible. In this regard, will the Chinese government consider chartered flights to evacuate overseas Chinese from some key countries?

In response, Zhu Tao, director of the Civil Aviation Administration of China, said that since March 4, the CAAC, on the basis of normal flight operations, has been targeting cities with concentrated demand and capable flight destinations, a major air transport guarantee mechanism has been activated, as appropriate, to operate temporary flights or charter flights.

So far, the Civil Aviation Administration of China has carried out 13 transportation missions to countries affected by the epidemic, including arranging seven temporary flights to pick up 1,101 Chinese citizens, carrying out one transportation mission of the Group of experts on foreign assistance, and transporting nine experts, 11.09 tons of goods and materials, 5 sorties of foreign aid, 78.45 tons of goods and materials. Zhu Tao said that in the next step, the CAAC will arrange such missions in a timely manner according to actual needs under the guidance of the Joint Defense and joint control mechanism of the State Council.

In response to whether passengers found to have symptoms of infection at the airport or at the centralized quarantine point will be treated on the spot or sent back to their countries of origin, a spokesman for the National Health Commission, Mi Feng, said that if relevant conditions are found during the centralized observation period, in accordance with China's laws and regulations, relevant personnel will be immediately sent to designated hospitals for screening and treatment.

Will the quarantine measures currently in place in Beijing be extended to all ports of entry, and will China consider a total ban on foreigners? In response, Mifeng said that Beijing has already taken relevant measures, and all localities will take corresponding management measures according to the actual situation and in accordance with laws and regulations.
